-- Saracens, Edinburgh, Cardiff Blues Reach Heineken Cup Rugby Quarterfinals
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-01-22T17:40:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-22/saracens-edinburgh-cardiff-blues-reach-heineken-cup-rugby-quarterfinals.html
Saracens won 26-20 at Treviso today
to top Pool 5 in rugby unionâ€™s Heineken Cup and become the only
English team to reach the quarterfinals. Edinburgh and  Cardiff
Blues  advanced from Pool 2.  Mouritz Botha and David Strettle got tries for Saracens,
with Owen Farrell kicking 16 points. Saracens will host Clermont
Auvergne in the quarterfinals.  Edinburgh topped Pool 2 following a 34-11 win against
 London Irish , with Cardiff through to the next round as one of
the two best second-place teams after a 36-30 victory over
Racing Metro.  Defending champion Leinster, fellow Irish team Munster,
Clermont and Toulouse were also group winners, while Ulster
secured the other runner-up spot.  Leinster is aiming to become the second team after
Leicester in 2001 and 2002 to win the competition in successive
years. Toulouse, Munster and Ulster are the other previous
champions still involved.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
